      "updated": 1775584341304,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Building the transfer edges that bridge the two\nlayers. A transfer edge says \"you can walk from\nthis street node to this stop in N seconds,\" and\nyou discover them via a spatial join: for each\nstop, query PostGIS (in case of using it ) for all\nstreet nodes within, say, 150 meters.",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "GdG517iwhLsHi70YREyyf",
      "originalText": "Building the transfer edges that bridge the two layers. A transfer edge says \"you can walk from this street node to this stop in N seconds,\" and you discover them via a spatial join: for each stop, query PostGIS (in case of using it ) for all street nodes within, say, 150 meters.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
